  "texts": [
    "As shown in Table 1, overall, the proposed fine-tuned U-Net with (composite) pose estimation loss (PEL) achieved improved landmark detection accuracy compared to the baseline U-Net and trained U-Net on PEL.",
    "All models performed better in the external test dataset -images that the models had not seen before -than in the internal test dataset.The baseline U-Net achieved mean RMSE values of 8.58 mm and 5.58 mm on internal and external datasets, respectively.",
    "The U-Net fine-tuned with PEL showed consistent improvements, achieving 8.45 mm (1.5% improvement) and 5.09 mm (8.8% improvement) on the respective datasets.The U-Net trained with composite PEL and with only PEL both showed a significant performance decline.",
    "Specifically, the U-Net trained with composite PEL had approximately 2.4 and 2.1 times increases in error relative to the baseline.",
    "This deterioration may be explained by the difference in optimization goals ingrained in the composite loss function."
  ],
